2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.990
<b>Big News</b>

3
00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:18.000
<b>Pangaea Castle
Mary Geoise</b>

4
00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:16.120
The World Conference,
also known as the Reverie...

5
00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:19.500
is a grand assembly of fifty kings and queens

6
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:25.760
that represents over 170 countries
affiliated with the World Government.

7
00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:28.760
It is held every four years.

8
00:00:34.970 --> 00:00:38.980
As always, the Reverie concluded
in a state of great confusion

9
00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.270
and all the representatives returned home.

10
00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:44.110
Then...

11
00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:48.320
one week later...

12
00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:53.200
Good grief... I'm finally home.

13
00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:53.200
<b>Ryugu Palace, Ryugu Kingdom
Fishman Island</b>

14
00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:58.160
Truly, the surface world is so far above us.

15
00:00:58.540 --> 00:01:02.170
Um, thank you so much for escorting us,

16
00:01:02.170 --> 00:01:04.500
Sir Luffy's grandfather!

17
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.420
It was a pretty long trip, huh, Neptune?

18
00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:09.670
You must be tired!

19
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:13.760
I'm exhausted.

20
00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:17.220
Garp, stay here with us
and replenish your energy.

21
00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:20.940
Well, maybe I'll have a cup of tea,

22
00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:24.940
but considering the situation,
I can't stay here for long.

23
00:01:26.610 --> 00:01:29.440
The Reverie always triggers big incidents.

24
00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:35.410
When fifty countries gather,
a simple "let's get along" won't suffice.

25
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:39.160
Each of them has their own internal troubles.

26
00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:43.170
Large and mighty countries
just stare quietly at each other

27
00:01:43.170 --> 00:01:45.500
and let their proxies bicker.

28
00:01:48.340 --> 00:01:52.430
They use resources
and technologies as leverage.

29
00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:59.270
They say that all countries
are on equal footing, but that's just talk.

30
00:01:59.810 --> 00:02:06.110
Wealth, poverty, and religious differences
won't allow them to be equal.

31
00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:16.320
Even if they appear to shake hands and smile,
they'll gladly step on each other's feet.

32
00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:23.080
I wonder how many leaders can speak for both
their citizens and those of other countries.

33
00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:25.420
It's only a roundtable in name.

34
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:30.210
You're right. Conversations among
the sovereigns were touch and go.

35
00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:36.550
We're no exception, but quarrels between
countries can't be solved so easily.

36
00:02:37.010 --> 00:02:39.220
The further a country's history extends,

37
00:02:39.220 --> 00:02:42.520
the deeper the roots of its conflict will grow.

38
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:49.190
Even if there is a disagreement,
as long as no blood is spilled, I call it peace.

39
00:02:50.190 --> 00:02:52.780
But what happened this time was pretty bad...

40
00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:58.570
This may be coming a bit late, but there's
one thing I haven't told you about yet.

41
00:02:58.570 --> 00:03:03.750
Right after the Reverie was dismissed
and we set off, an incident occurred,

42
00:03:04.080 --> 00:03:06.500
I received a report while aboard our ship.

43
00:03:07.460 --> 00:03:11.920
We Marines will do our best
to resolve it, but please don't fear

44
00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:15.340
the surface world or us humans!

45
00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:17.840
An incident...?

46
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:21.600
Garp, what kind of report did you receive?

47
00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:25.600
The incident concerns
the Kingdom of Alabasta.

48
00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:27.560
The Kingdom of Alabasta...

49
00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.360
Princess Vivi!

50
00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:35.320
Before all of this transpired...

51
00:03:35.860 --> 00:03:39.620
At the World Economic News,
right after the Reverie was dismissed...

52
00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:43.240
Unbelievable! It's incident after incident!

53
00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:46.120
I can't believe so much happened at once...

54
00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:49.330
Listen up! Find me
the greatest headline yet!

55
00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:53.710
Sir, which one should make the front page?!

56
00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:56.970
Listen! We have a death on our hands!

57
00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:59.840
<b>Editor-in-Chief Morgans
World Economic Newspaper</b>

58
00:03:56.970 --> 00:03:59.840
Big obituaries move papers!

59
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:00.970
Then, the headli–

60
00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:02.470
No, wait!

61
00:04:02.470 --> 00:04:04.720
The resolution they passed is also good.

62
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:08.230
But a murder attempt is exciting as well!

63
00:04:08.230 --> 00:04:09.400
That's right!

64
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:11.270
Okay, let's have two front pages!

65
00:04:11.270 --> 00:04:13.520
The back page will have the same format!

66
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:14.820
– Okay!
– Okay!

67
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:16.400
Sir.

68
00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.360
Express mail from the government.

69
00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:20.780
A check, huh?

70
00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:23.030
Oh, that's a lot!

71
00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:26.290
I see. It's an order to manipulate information.

72
00:04:26.290 --> 00:04:28.660
But for which affair?

73
00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:35.340
Hushing up this incident?!

74
00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:36.840
No way in hell!

75
00:04:37.380 --> 00:04:39.340
Throw this back in their faces!

76
00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:41.340
Hey, what's wrong?

77
00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:43.390
My, my, my...

78
00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:49.520
Do as you're told, Morgans!

79
00:04:49.520 --> 00:04:50.730
The secret agency,

80
00:04:50.730 --> 00:04:52.150
Cipher Pol?!

81
00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:55.980
You must obey orders
from the World Government.

82
00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:56.860
Don't move!

83
00:05:01.450 --> 00:05:05.870
Never underestimate Big News Morgans!

84
00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.630
When did he sneak in?

85
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:17.130
Sir! Members of Cipher Pol
are government officials!

86
00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:18.260
I know!

87
00:05:18.260 --> 00:05:20.470
It's dangerous to stay here, guys.

88
00:05:20.470 --> 00:05:22.340
Let's fly!

89
00:05:25.970 --> 00:05:28.220
I may be avaricious,

90
00:05:28.220 --> 00:05:31.310
but I am first and foremost a journalist!

91
00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:33.730
I make people dance to the tune of my lies.

92
00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:35.440
I'm a DJ of words!

93
00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:39.400
I decide what to publish!

94
00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:44.940
Mr. Morgans!

95
00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:47.700
You have a call from King Wapol!

96
00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:49.120
King Wapol?

97
00:05:51.040 --> 00:05:52.870
What does he want?

98
00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:56.090
Well, it sounds like he has information to leak.

99
00:05:56.090 --> 00:05:58.170
What?!

100
00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:10.020
What's going on?

101
00:06:10.020 --> 00:06:11.100
A special report?

102
00:06:19.030 --> 00:06:19.940
Don't worry...

103
00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:21.860
It'll be all right.

104
00:06:29.200 --> 00:06:32.540
With the government's failure
to hush up what had happened,

105
00:06:32.540 --> 00:06:37.290
the decisions the leaders made at the Reverie,
as well as the incidents that occurred there,

106
00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:42.090
instantly became known throughout the world
and left many people in shock.

107
00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:44.930
Vayyt!

108
00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:46.340
Vhaat the hell is this?!

109
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:57.060
<b>Revolutionary Army Headquarters
Kamabakka Queendom</b>

110
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.350
This cannot be true!

111
00:06:51.350 --> 00:06:53.480
It is just a story in the paper, right?

112
00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:57.060
That is just the WEN! Their bird president
must have written nonsense!

113
00:06:57.610 --> 00:06:59.520
I am sure of it!

114
00:07:02.940 --> 00:07:04.820
This is Sabo after all!

115
00:07:04.820 --> 00:07:06.450
It just cannot be...

116
00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:08.660
I do not buy it!

117
00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:09.780
Calm down!

118
00:07:10.410 --> 00:07:13.620
First, we must confirm the facts.

119
00:07:13.620 --> 00:07:16.040
But with all of them out of contact...

120
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.630
how can we confirm?

121
00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:21.000
It's not true, is it?

122
00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:23.800
Sabo...

123
00:07:25.130 --> 00:07:27.800
<b>Royal Escort Ship
Kingdom of Goa</b>

124
00:07:26.590 --> 00:07:27.800
My lady!

125
00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:29.850
He was in Mary Geoise?!

126
00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:32.890
M-My brother?!

127
00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:40.400
<b>Windmill Village
Kingdom of Goa</b>

128
00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:37.430
What happened to Makino?

129
00:07:37.430 --> 00:07:39.230
The bar is closed today.

130
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:40.400
What?!

131
00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:43.610
So much has happened in the world...

132
00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:45.610
I could use a drink.

133
00:07:48.860 --> 00:07:50.370
Sabo is...

134
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:59.040
<b>Mt. Colubo
Kingdom of Goa</b>

135
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:56.500
And I had just learned he was still alive...

136
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.040
Tell me it's not true!

137
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:04.210
Sabo!

138
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:09.680
<b>Undersea Prison Impel Down</b>

139
00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:14.430
I never get bored with this world!

140
00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:17.600
It's getting interesting!

141
00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:27.280
Hey, guys!

142
00:08:25.070 --> 00:08:27.280
<b>Beehive
Pirate Island</b>

143
00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:29.030
Let's set sail!

144
00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:31.620
Instead of watching
the Marines snatch it away,

145
00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:34.540
I'll take it for myself!

146
00:08:39.420 --> 00:08:42.330
And now, we return to the present...

147
00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:50.930
<b>The Outskirts 
of Ebisu Town

Wano</b>

148
00:08:57.600 --> 00:08:59.350
Koby, it's me.

149
00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:04.940
<b>Present Day
A Stretch of Open Sea</b>

150
00:09:03.730 --> 00:09:04.940
Hold on a second.

151
00:09:05.320 --> 00:09:07.110
Let me go somewhere private.

152
00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:07.690
Okay.

153
00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:13.370
Oh, yeah! Sea!

154
00:09:13.700 --> 00:09:14.700
Fog!

155
00:09:16.410 --> 00:09:17.830
As always,

156
00:09:17.830 --> 00:09:19.000
you're a stickler.

157
00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:22.500
Well, it is a rule...

158
00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:24.170
Oh, right! It's terrible!

159
00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:26.670
There's something I need to report to you,

160
00:09:27.250 --> 00:09:28.260
Commander!

161
00:09:28.380 --> 00:09:33.130
<b>X Drake
Marine Headquarters
Officer of SWORD, a Top Secret Special Force</b>

162
00:09:37.010 --> 00:09:38.470
What?!

163
00:09:38.470 --> 00:09:40.850
That's the situation?!

164
00:09:41.190 --> 00:09:43.980
Yeah. Even with all
the Marines in the world

165
00:09:43.980 --> 00:09:47.270
it's too much to handle.

166
00:09:44.020 --> 00:09:47.270
<b>Captain Koby
Marine Headquarters
Member of SWORD</b>

167
00:09:47.270 --> 00:09:49.820
So just as we planned,

168
00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:53.030
the Marines won't get involved
with what's going on over there.

169
00:09:53.030 --> 00:09:54.870
They don't have enough manpower.

170
00:09:54.870 --> 00:09:56.370
That's fine.

171
00:09:56.370 --> 00:09:59.200
Wano isn't affiliated with
the World Government.

172
00:09:59.660 --> 00:10:03.790
Now, about Big Mom arriving at Onigashima...

173
00:10:03.790 --> 00:10:04.500
Yes.

174
00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:08.710
Kaido and Big Mom
have been at odds for so long

175
00:10:08.710 --> 00:10:12.090
that the Marines are hoping those
two pirates will ruin each other.

176
00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:13.630
Yeah, I guess.

177
00:10:13.630 --> 00:10:18.850
As we expected, Kaido and Big Mom
were at each other's throats...

178
00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:22.020
but now they've joined hands!

179
00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:28.270
Wh-Wh-Wh-What do you mean?!

180
00:10:32.110 --> 00:10:35.870
As for Straw Hat Luffy,
there's been no word of a breakout.

181
00:10:36.490 --> 00:10:38.740
The situation is at a standstill.

182
00:10:38.740 --> 00:10:41.120
There's also one more unpleasant thing.

183
00:10:41.120 --> 00:10:44.080
I saw Cipher Pol 0 in the capital the other day.

184
00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:46.210
What?! Why are they in Wano?!

185
00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:49.380
I hope I'm wrong,

186
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:52.590
but it must mean the World Government

187
00:10:52.590 --> 00:10:56.180
is doing business with Wano,
a country ruled by a pirate.

188
00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:00.010
When I found out,

189
00:11:00.510 --> 00:11:03.430
I was stunned for a few minutes.

190
00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:15.910
By the way, where are you now?

191
00:11:15.910 --> 00:11:16.610
Right.

192
00:11:17.410 --> 00:11:20.950
We're heading toward the Isle of Women...

193
00:11:25.500 --> 00:11:28.080
to capture Pirate Empress Boa Hancock!

194
00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:29.790
Oh, my...

195
00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:33.840
Those ships coming toward us
over the Calm Belt...

196
00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:35.630
Is that a Marine fleet?!

197
00:11:36.590 --> 00:11:38.680
Marguerite!

198
00:11:38.680 --> 00:11:41.560
What's going to happen?!

199
00:11:43.810 --> 00:11:46.770
The news spread all around the world.

200
00:11:47.770 --> 00:11:50.480
They should have done this a long time ago!

201
00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:53.110
It was a mistake to team up with pirates...

202
00:11:53.780 --> 00:11:54.860
They're evil!

203
00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:58.280
For those who think all pirates are bad...

204
00:12:00.370 --> 00:12:03.200
Those government dogs will finally go away!

205
00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:07.080
Screw that Pirate Empress,
Hawk Eye, and Clown!

206
00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:10.210
They're nothing but looters!

207
00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:15.300
...and for those who hate looters,
it's good news.

208
00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:19.800
But I thought they did great
in the Summit War!

209
00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:22.220
That's what they decided?!

210
00:12:22.760 --> 00:12:25.140
The Marines are ready
to take immediate action.

211
00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:26.430
Is this really wise?

212
00:12:26.430 --> 00:12:30.100
They were one of the world's
three great powers!

213
00:12:30.100 --> 00:12:33.730
For those who knew of
their feats in the Summit War,

214
00:12:33.730 --> 00:12:38.490
and those who were concerned about disrupting
the balance of the three great powers,

215
00:12:38.490 --> 00:12:40.990
it was truly an alarming situation.

216
00:12:43.870 --> 00:12:49.540
The news story from the latest Reverie
that stunned people across the world the most...

217
00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:51.040
was...

218
00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:54.210
the abolition...

219
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:56.340
of the Seven Warlords system!

220
00:12:57.880 --> 00:13:02.760
The Seven Warlords of the Sea were pirates
officially recognized by the government.

221
00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:05.180
While they were allowed to pillage,

222
00:13:05.180 --> 00:13:10.100
the government used them
as deterrents against other pirates.

223
00:13:10.100 --> 00:13:15.730
The roster of the Seven Warlords
has changed over time.

224
00:13:22.070 --> 00:13:23.410
Crocodile.

225
00:13:23.950 --> 00:13:28.870
He clashed with the Straw Hats
over the Kingdom of Alabasta.

226
00:13:28.870 --> 00:13:31.750
He was trying to take over the kingdom

227
00:13:31.750 --> 00:13:35.840
but was ultimately defeated by Luffy
and expelled from the Seven Warlords.

228
00:13:36.750 --> 00:13:40.170
The man who replaced Crocodile
and joined the Seven Warlords...

229
00:13:40.170 --> 00:13:42.430
was Marshall D. Teach.

230
00:13:42.430 --> 00:13:48.890
However, he announced his resignation
after achieving his goal.

231
00:13:50.180 --> 00:13:52.140
Jinbe, Knight of the Sea,

232
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:54.940
opposed the Summit War and grew
disdainful of the Marines.

233
00:13:55.650 --> 00:13:58.610
He, too, declared his resignation.

234
00:14:01.860 --> 00:14:03.700
Gecko Moria.

235
00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:10.000
This man who had once clashed with the Straw Hats
was also called to the Summit War.

236
00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:12.120
However...

237
00:14:13.540 --> 00:14:17.800
just after the war, an order for an ambush
came from high up in the government,

238
00:14:17.800 --> 00:14:19.630
and he was expelled.

239
00:14:20.550 --> 00:14:23.510
Heavenly Demon Donquixote Doflamingo.

240
00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:28.180
All while governing Dressrosa as its king,

241
00:14:28.180 --> 00:14:33.770
he trafficked an artificial devil fruit, SMILE,
as an influential underground broker.

242
00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:35.440
However...

243
00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:39.770
he lost the kingdom in a struggle
against Luffy's alliance,

244
00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:41.990
and his title of Warlord was revoked.

245
00:14:42.440 --> 00:14:45.160
And finally, Trafalgar Law.

246
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:49.120
He allied himself with the Straw Hats
to take down Doflamingo...

247
00:14:49.790 --> 00:14:52.250
and was stripped of his title.

248
00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:56.630
The four pirates who reign supreme
as if they're emperors:

249
00:14:58.250 --> 00:14:59.420
the Four Emperors.

250
00:15:00.340 --> 00:15:03.220
And trying to contain them:
Marine Headquarters.

251
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:06.550
Last but not least:
The Seven Warlords of the Sea.

252
00:15:06.130 --> 00:15:12.930
<b>The Seven Warlords of the Sea</b>

253
00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:11.390
These three great powers
have kept the world at peace.

254
00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:12.930
<b>The Four Emperors Navy</b>

255
00:15:11.970 --> 00:15:12.930
However,

256
00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:16.690
two kings had suffered terribly
at the hands of Warlords:

257
00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:20.020
King Nefertari Cobra
of the Kingdom of Alabasta,

258
00:15:20.610 --> 00:15:23.780
and Riku Doldo III
of the Kingdom of Dressrosa.

259
00:15:23.780 --> 00:15:26.860
They fought for the abolition
of the Seven Warlords system.

260
00:15:27.530 --> 00:15:31.080
Then, after a heated debate at the Reverie,

261
00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:35.460
a large majority supported
the proposition, and it passed.

262
00:15:36.710 --> 00:15:42.300
Therefore, the Seven Warlords of the Sea
will automatically be stripped of all their rights,

263
00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:46.180
and their connection with
the World Government will hereby be cut off.

264
00:15:46.180 --> 00:15:47.010
That means...!

265
00:15:47.010 --> 00:15:50.470
<b>Empty Bluffs Island
New World</b>

266
00:15:47.890 --> 00:15:49.260
Buggy,

267
00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:53.270
you're just another pirate!

268
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:56.390
That's no fair, you assholes!

269
00:15:56.390 --> 00:16:01.440
A decision was made without telling us,
and since we're no longer useful, you arrest us?!

270
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:03.650
You have no sense of justice whatsoever!

271
00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:08.240
Whether Crocodile and Doflamingo
outsmarted you is none of my business!

272
00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:11.240
Don't take it out on me!

273
00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:13.830
They've got the whole coast surrounded!

274
00:16:14.330 --> 00:16:15.870
What should we do?

275
00:16:16.910 --> 00:16:20.790
My entire life's plan is going to the dogs!

276
00:16:21.290 --> 00:16:22.250
Oh?

277
00:16:22.290 --> 00:16:27.720
<b>An Island
in the New World</b>

278
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:25.920
The Marines should be on our side,
but they've surrounded us!

279
00:16:25.920 --> 00:16:27.720
What should we do, Mommy?!

280
00:16:28.300 --> 00:16:30.180
Mommy!

281
00:16:31.640 --> 00:16:35.060
<b>The Ruins of the Muggy Kingdom
Gloom Island</b>

282
00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:33.560
Surrender yourself now,

283
00:16:33.560 --> 00:16:35.060
Hawk Eye Mihawk!

284
00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:37.680
Surrender yourself now!

285
00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:42.150
<b>The Isle of Women
Amazon Lily</b>

286
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:42.150
Snyake Princess, we have a problem!

287
00:16:42.150 --> 00:16:46.440
Your title of Warlord has been stripped away!

288
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:48.360
Elder Nyon!

289
00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:50.320
There are Marine ships off the coast!

290
00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:51.530
What?!

291
00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:54.160
They've already gone into action?!

292
00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:56.580
Don't panic!

293
00:16:57.910 --> 00:16:59.210
Snyake Princess!

294
00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:01.750
They've obviously forgotten something...

295
00:17:03.460 --> 00:17:04.710
don't you think?

296
00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:07.970
This is no good, President Buggy!

297
00:17:07.970 --> 00:17:09.380
Should we run?!

298
00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:14.050
Of course not! We'll show them a flashy fight!

299
00:17:18.680 --> 00:17:23.900
Show some guts, you sad sacks!

300
00:17:25.190 --> 00:17:27.780
– That's our President Buggy!
– That's our President Buggy!

301
00:17:27.810 --> 00:17:29.650
<b>Former Warlord of the Sea</b>

302
00:17:27.850 --> 00:17:27.940
<b>Buggy's Delivery Chairman Buggy "the Bombastic Clown"</b>

303
00:17:27.850 --> 00:17:33.190
<b>Buggy's Delivery</b>
<b>Chairman Buggy "the Bombastic Clown"</b>

304
00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:33.200
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!

305
00:17:29.650 --> 00:17:33.190
<b>Former Warlord of the Sea</b>

306
00:17:33.530 --> 00:17:36.700
Seems like they're not on our side anymore!

307
00:17:36.700 --> 00:17:39.370
How incredibly unforgivable...

308
00:17:39.370 --> 00:17:40.910
Weevil!

309
00:17:40.910 --> 00:17:43.000
You have permission to take them down!

310
00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:44.800
R-Really?!

311
00:17:44.800 --> 00:17:48.050
In that case, I'm gonna kill 'em...

312
00:17:48.290 --> 00:17:52.590
<b>Edward "Whitebeard Jr. (Self-Proclaimed)" Weevil
Former Warlord of the Sea</b>

313
00:17:49.630 --> 00:17:52.590
in the name of Whitebeard!

314
00:17:53.260 --> 00:17:54.890
I feel a tremor of excitement.

315
00:17:55.640 --> 00:17:57.260
It's been a long time...

316
00:17:57.350 --> 00:17:59.010
<b>Dracule Mihawk
"Hawk Eye" Former Warlord 
of the Sea</b>

317
00:17:57.350 --> 00:17:57.390
<b>Former Warlord 
of the Sea</b>

318
00:17:57.560 --> 00:17:57.760
<b>Former Warlord</b>

319
00:17:57.680 --> 00:17:57.760
<b>Dracule Mihawk</b>

320
00:17:59.010 --> 00:18:03.810
<b>Dracule Mihawk
"Hawk Eye" Former Warlord 
of the Sea</b>

321
00:17:59.270 --> 00:18:02.190
since I was the one being hunted.

322
00:18:03.810 --> 00:18:03.850
<b>Dracule Mihawk
"Hawk Eye" Former Warlord 
of the Sea</b>

323
00:18:03.850 --> 00:18:07.400
We became the Seven Warlords of the Sea...

324
00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:07.810
<b>"Pirate Empress" Boa Hancock
Former Warlord of the Sea</b>

325
00:18:07.640 --> 00:18:12.730
<b>"Pirate Empress" Boa Hancock</b>
<b>Former Warlord of the Sea "Pirate Empress" Boa Hancock
Former Warlord of the Sea</b>

326
00:18:09.900 --> 00:18:12.740
because of our might!

327
00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:16.070
I'm counting on you guys.

328
00:18:16.070 --> 00:18:18.200
In the meantime...

329
00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:22.210
I'll get the hell out of here...
